As summer arrives, so too does high jewelry season, ushering in a dynamic calendar of launches, destination presentations, and creative collaborations.
@pomellato brought the 2026 high jewelry season to a dazzling close in Paris with “Stile Libero”—“Freestyle”—a 65-piece collection that revels in color and craft. Unfolding across three chapters (Visionary Colors, Magnetic Gold, and Hypnotic Shadows), the collection channels the maison’s most recognizable codes: saturated gemstones, sculptural goldwork, and settings that feel anything but conventional.
At the link in bio, read more from ELLE’s executive fashion and accessories director @awolfestyle on Pomellato’s new collection as well as all the other jewelry-related happenings worth knowing about.

