posts.caption:
@pharrell wore the exact same @louisvuitton look to take his bow after LV Spring/Summer 2027 and to @dior menswear show the next morning. Same Richard Mille x Ferrari watch, same yellow shades, same backwards monogram cap, even the same little LV fanny pack. Normally, outfit repeating isn't news, but when it's Pharrell, it says something about where Louis Vuitton is headed.⁠
⁠
Three years into his tenure, Pharrell's latest Louis Vuitton collection marks a shift away from the flashier days of million-dollar bags and bootcut rodeo fits. Spring/Summer 2027 delivers a more refined, understated vision, pairing luxe craftsmanship with effortless classics. His now signature combo of jeans, a grey zip hoodie, croc sneakers, and statement accessories perfectly reflects that new mood: relaxed, Cali-coded, and unmistakably Louis Vuitton.⁠

