@adidasoriginals has turned Paris into a giant Stan Smith tribute. Kicking things off by wrapping the iconic Opéra Garnier in the sneaker’s signature green, the brand plans to spread the unmistakable shade across rooftops, facades, street furniture, and more throughout the city. 

Why green you may ask? Well, It’s a reminder of how a simple green heel tab became one of fashion’s most recognizable design details.

📸 @easternspy

posts.caption:
@arcteryx has quietly dropped one of its loudest jackets yet. Buried among the brand's technical outerwear is the new Norvan Windshell Hoody, a lightweight performance shell that swaps stealth for supersized branding, with oversized Arc'teryx lettering and its signature "Deadbird" fossil logo stretched across the sleeves.⁠
⁠
It feels like another sign of Arc'teryx leaning into its status as the outerwear brand of choice for the style-conscious wellness crowd. Technical gear left the trail for the city long ago, and this logofied windshell proves performance apparel isn't getting any quieter, it's just getting more fashion-forward.⁠

