@commedesgarcons HOMME PLUS Spring/Summer 2027 collection, *If The War Were To End..*, brought together many of Rei Kawakubo's signature design codes, from ballooning trousers and clashing tartans to warped tailoring and chopped-up shirting. But despite the collection's impressively wearable lineup, one familiar silhouette stole the show.⁠
⁠
Over a decade after they first appeared, COMME des GARÇONS HOMME PLUS' pointy Mexican dancing boots are back. Created once again with French shoemaker Mexicana, the dramatic Guarachero-inspired boots mark the rare return of one of the brand's most recognizable designs, proving that even a label built on constant reinvention knows when to revisit a classic.⁠

